    "course_title": "EARTH'S WATER: NATURAL SCIENCE AND HUMAN USE",
    "description": "Water is central to the functioning of planet Earth. As humans increase their impact on Earth's systems and cohabitants, our understanding of the multiple roles of water becomes critical to finding sustainable strategies for human and ecosystem health. Explores the science of Earth's hydrosphere, with constant attention to human uses and impacts.",
